  "body": "### What is wrong?\r\nAs [sharding spec](https://github.com/ethereum/sharding/blob/develop/docs/doc.md#create_collation) pointed, we need `GUESS_HEAD` to  \"pick the longest valid chain, check validity as far as possible, and if you find it's invalid then switch to the next-highest-scoring valid chain you know about\", once we find ourselves the eligible proposer.\r\n\r\n### How can it be fixed\r\n- Implement it with the mocked `fetch_and_verify_collation`.\r\n- Start with one process(At first we don't consider the case with multiprocess)\r\n    - Use `timer` or `blockFilter` to see when to return from the function\r\n\r\n\r\n#### TODO list (To be completed)\r\n- [ ] Might need to solve https://github.com/ethereum/py-evm/issues/344",
